  "skeletons": {
    "results_md": "## R28 \u00b7 Geometry auxiliary-construction repair \u2014 [SLOT: verdict headline \u2014 write it from the numbers below]\n\nPopulation: 2D pruned distance-geometry chains the reference pipeline (scipy LM, k_refine=4) fails as posed under two independent restart streams; each arm's chosen construction gets one more reference solve on a fresh common stream (`run_geo_repair.py`).  Data seed 20260722 is shared across optimization seeds 11/29/47, so the failure pools coincide; flip rates are mean \u00b1 population SD over the 3 seeds.  Labels and flips are budget-relative measurements at the reference budget \u2014 NOT CAS certificates; do not reuse R10's certificate language here.\n\n| arm | trained-k (N=67) | transfer-k (N=64) |\n|---|---:|---:|\n| ranker | 0.233 \u00b1 0.007 | 0.157 \u00b1 0.036 |\n| recipe_only | 0.207 \u00b1 0.014 | 0.179 \u00b1 0.022 |\n| random | 0.207 \u00b1 0.013 | 0.130 \u00b1 0.010 |\n| best_fixed | 0.195 \u00b1 0.052 | 0.113 \u00b1 0.042 |\n| all_cos | 0.222 \u00b1 0.022 | 0.119 \u00b1 0.004 |\n| restart_control | 0.243 \u00b1 0.007 | 0.190 \u00b1 0.009 |\n| restart_plus16 | 0.539 \u00b1 0.001 | 0.499 \u00b1 0.023 |\n| restart_plus32 | 0.731 \u00b1 0.001 | 0.755 \u00b1 0.007 |\n| probe | 0.683 \u00b1 0.023 | 0.751 \u00b1 0.023 |\n| enumeration | 0.616 \u00b1 0.018 | 0.629 \u00b1 0.041 |\n\nPaired comparisons \u2014 exact McNemar on the common e2e stream, primary seed 11, Holm-corrected within each pool over the declared 6-comparison family; the other seeds are raw-p robustness columns:\n\n| ranker vs | trained W/L | trained p (Holm) | transfer W/L | transfer p (Holm) | raw p, other seeds (trained) |\n|---|---:|---:|---:|---:|---|\n| restart_control | 3/5 | 1.000 | 3/3 | 1.000 | 0.613 (s29), 0.656 (s47) |\n| random | 7/6 | 1.000 | 8/4 | 0.969 | 0.500 (s29), 0.291 (s47) |\n| recipe_only | 5/5 | 1.000 | 4/4 | 1.000 | 0.377 (s29), 0.227 (s47) |\n| best_fixed | 1/4 | 1.000 | 5/3 | 1.000 | 0.133 (s29), 0.113 (s47) |\n| all_cos | 6/8 | 1.000 | 7/2 | 0.539 | 0.387 (s29), 0.377 (s47) |\n| probe | 1/34 | 1.000 | 3/36 | 1.000 | 1.000 (s29), 1.000 (s47) |\n\nCost (restarts per instance, mean over seeds): ranker 4.0, probe 19.7, restart_plus32 32.0, enumeration 78.0.\n\nLabel-vs-e2e agreement proxy (seed 11, all 131 test rows): \"label stream found \u22651 working construction\" vs \"enumeration flipped on the e2e stream\" agree on 94/131 = 0.718 [0.635,0.788] (label+/e2e\u2212 16, label\u2212/e2e+ 21).  Random-arm calibration: flip 0.176 vs 0.169 expected from mean(n_working/n_candidates).  Per-candidate top1-hit agreement is not derivable from the stored rows; rerun with the per-candidate label vector stored per row to get it.\n\nEvidence: results/p_geo_repair/geo_repair_s{11,29,47}.json, results/p_geo_repair/analysis.json.\n[SLOT: PROVENANCE row \u2014 command, seeds, commit]",
    "marc_tex": "% --- R28 geometry construction repair (generated by analyze_geo_repair.py; verify before pasting) ---\nOn pruned distance-geometry chains the reference pipeline fails as posed (two independent restart streams; $N=67$ trained-$k$, $N=64$ held-out-$k$ failures), the construction ranker flips $0.233 \\pm 0.007$ of the trained-$k$ pool at one augmented reference solve, against $0.243 \\pm 0.007$ for the matched-budget restart control and $0.539 \\pm 0.001$/$0.731 \\pm 0.001$ at $+16$/$+32$ restarts; the no-learning construction arms reach $0.195 \\pm 0.052$ (best fixed), $0.222 \\pm 0.022$ (all cosine lifts) and $0.207 \\pm 0.014$ (recipe-only ranker).\nExact paired McNemar tests on the common stream, Holm-corrected over the six-comparison family, give p=1.000 (raw p other seeds: 0.613, 0.656) against the restart control, p=1.000 (raw p other seeds: 0.133, 0.113) against best-fixed and p=1.000 (raw p other seeds: 0.387, 0.377) against all-cos on the primary seed (seeds 11/29/47, mean $\\pm$ population SD).\nThe probe control reaches $0.683 \\pm 0.023$ at 19.7 restarts per instance versus the ranker's 4.0, and enumeration bounds the ceiling at $0.616 \\pm 0.018$ at 78.0.\nOn the held-out-$k$ pool the ranker flips $0.157 \\pm 0.036$ versus $0.190 \\pm 0.009$ for the restart control (p=1.000 (raw p other seeds: 1.000, 0.984)) and $0.113 \\pm 0.042$ for best-fixed (p=1.000 (raw p other seeds: 0.145, 0.344)).\nLabels and flips are budget-relative measurements at the reference-solver budget, not certificates.\n[SLOT: claim sentence \u2014 write only after checking the ranker-vs-best\\_fixed/all\\_cos direction; if a fixed construction is competitive, report it as the honest ceiling.]"
